OL,6, And my word did it do untold damage to 
OL,7, my psyche as a kid. I remember staying 
OL,8, at my Grandma's one night and the      
OL,9, Meridian logo suddenly appearing at the
OL,10, end of some programme on the TV. Being 
OL,11, very young, I was frightened to death  
OL,12, by it. So much so that I had trouble   
OL,13, sleeping that night, and that in the   
OL,14, future whenever I was given the choice 
OL,15, of staying overnight at my Nan's house 
OL,16, or at Grandma's, for several years     
OL,17, afterwards I always chose Nan's without
OL,18, fail, resolute in my fear that that    
OL,19, intrusive and unnerving face of fire   
OL,20, was waiting at Grandma's to sneak into 
OL,21, my hastily prepared bedroom and petrify
OL,22, my soul. 
